# Manual & API Testing Project | Evershop Demo Website

> A complete industry-style Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC) project performed on the Evershop Demo Website. This project demonstrates requirement analysis, test planning, manual test design, test execution, defect reporting, UI validation, REST API testing using Postman, and API automation using Newman.

---

# Project Overview

This project simulates the responsibilities of a Software QA Engineer by following an end-to-end testing workflow used in software companies.

Instead of focusing only on test case writing or API testing, this project starts from understanding business requirements and proceeds through every major phase of the Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC), including:

- Requirement Analysis
- Test Planning
- Test Scenario Design
- Manual Test Case Creation
- Manual Test Execution
- Defect Reporting
- UI Validation
- REST API Testing
- API Automation using Newman
- Test Reporting

The application under test is the **Evershop Demo E-commerce Website**, where both frontend functionality and backend REST APIs were thoroughly validated.

---

# Project Objectives

- Understand business and functional requirements.
- Design comprehensive manual test cases.
- Validate core e-commerce functionalities.
- Identify and document software defects.
- Perform UI verification through manual execution.
- Validate REST APIs using Postman.
- Automate API execution using Newman.
- Generate detailed execution reports.

---

