# Requirement Analysis

The project begins with analyzing the software requirements before any testing activities.

The requirement analysis includes:

- Business Requirements
- Functional Requirements
- Non-functional Requirements
- User Stories
- Acceptance Criteria
- Assumptions
- Scope Identification

This phase ensures that testing is aligned with business expectations.

---

# Manual Test Design

Comprehensive manual test cases were created by considering both positive and negative scenarios.

The test cases include:

- Test Scenario ID
- Test Case ID
- Module
- Preconditions
- Test Steps
- Expected Results
- Actual Results
- Priority
- Severity
- Status

The designed test cases cover various functional areas of the application.

---

# Manual Test Execution

All designed test cases were executed manually on the Evershop Demo Website.

Execution evidence is included with screenshots for every important scenario.

Executed modules include:

- Product Search
- Search Suggestions
- Product Listing
- Product Variants
- Cart Operations
- Search Validation
- Negative Search
- Multilingual Search
- Invalid Search
- UI Verification

---

# Defect Reporting

During execution several defects were identified and documented.

Each defect includes:

- Bug ID
- Summary
- Description
- Severity
- Priority
- Preconditions
- Steps to Reproduce
- Expected Result
- Actual Result
- Status
- Supporting Screenshot

Example defects include:

- Search returns incorrect product variant
- Voice search functionality missing
- Conversational search not implemented
- Product search inconsistency
- Search filtering issues

---

# UI Testing

The UI testing validates different user interactions including:

### Search Functionality

- Exact product search
- Partial keyword search
- Search suggestions
- Invalid search
- Empty search
- Multilingual input
- Special character validation

### Search Result Validation

Verified:

- Product names
- Search suggestions
- No-result messages
- Product listing
- Navigation behavior

---

# API Testing

REST APIs were tested using Postman.

The API collection validates complete cart functionality.

### APIs Covered

### Search Product

- GET

Validated:

- Status Code
- Response Structure
- Product List
- Product Name
- Product SKU
- Product Price

---

### View Cart

- GET

Validated:

- Cart Items
- Product Quantity
- Cart UUID
- Item UUID

---

### Add to Cart

- POST

Validated:

- Status Code
- Product Addition
- Quantity
- Cart Creation
- Dynamic Product Selection

---

### Increase Product Quantity

- PATCH

Validated:

- Quantity Increment
- Updated Response
- Business Logic Validation

---

### Decrease Product Quantity

- PATCH

Validated:

- Quantity Decrement
- Updated Quantity
- Response Validation

---

### Remove Product

- DELETE

Validated:

- Product Removal
- Product SKU
- Successful Deletion
- Error Handling

---

# Dynamic API Validation

JavaScript was used extensively inside Postman for dynamic testing.

Implemented features include:

- Collection Variables
- Dynamic Product Selection
- Random Product Generation
- Quantity Validation
- UUID Extraction
- JSON Parsing
- Response Validation
- Business Logic Assertions
- Error Handling using try-catch

---

# API Automation

The Postman collection was automated using Newman CLI.

Automation includes:

- Command Line Execution
- Automated Assertion Execution
- Console Logging
- HTML Report Generation

Example command:

```bash
newman run API_Testing.postman_collection.json
```

